CENG 4341 - Civil Engineers and Leadership, Public Policy,
Business Practices, and Asset Management
Civil Engineers are required to be leaders of their communities as well
as their firms. Leadership, public policy, business practices, and asset
management are critical areas that a civil engineer must have skills in,
albeit the skills that allow entry at the engineer in training level. This
course will tie these required skills to tasks Civil Engineers are required
to perform. Three lectures per week.
Prerequisite: Department Chair approval, Senior standing.
